Epigyne (Fig. 41
E-G
): posterior margin of the scape weakly sclerotized and straight (Fig. 41E). Scape short and squared, wider than the spermathecae, with a convex posterior margin (Fig. 41F). Copulatory ducts straight and swollen (Fig. 41G), fertilization ducts twisted into two or three loops before reaching the spermathecae (Fig. 41G). Spermathecae approximately globular, as wide as the copulatory ducts, separated by about 1.5 diameters (Fig. 41
F-G
).
